--- benjamin@... wrote:
> junit.framework.AssertionFailedError: Wrong country 
>
expected:<ethenticate/Country:com.notuskey.persistence.whoWhere.Countr
> yPK@e0> but 
>
was:<ethenticate/Country:com.notuskey.persistence.whoWhere.CountryPK@e
> 0>
> 
> which puzzles me, because it looks like they are equal. But I am new 
> to JUnit and I might not get it.

assertEquals calls object.equals(otherObject), and puts
object.toString() and otherObject.toString() in the Error. Perhaps you
have two objects that print the same, but are not .equals to each
other. Sounds like it might be a defect in either toString() or
equals().
